<div id="wrapper"><h2><a href="/output/Page2.asp"><img alt="" height="70" src="../files/images/XM_logo.gif" title="XM London Digital Communication" width="162" /></a></h2><h2><img width="190" alt="Case histories" height="80" border="0" src="/files/images/XM_L3_Clients_histories_shdr.gif" /></h2><p><strong>SaBRE</strong></p><p>Reservists play an increasingly important role in the armed forces and SaBRE (Supporting Britain's Reservists and Employers)  is a Ministry of Defence campaign that  aims to raise awareness of the Volunteer Reserve Forcesamong employers and decision makers.</p><p>The site has a key role in keeping employers of Reservists informed, providing detailed information on the benefits of employing Reservists, the roles and responsibilities of Reservists, the mobilisation process and the support services available to both employers and Reservists.</p><p>The site provides extensive information regarding legislation, financial support, case studies and important SaBRE contacts. The site has several forms that capture data, allowing employers to begin the 'become a supportive employer' process online. Users can sign up to receive email alerts and the site also includes a large Photo Library and a full set of downloadable SaBRE publications.</p><p>SaBRE can edit and maintain all content through the NetDevPlus CMS and quickly add important items through an integrated news manager and mail manager.</p><p><a href="http://www.sabre.mod.uk/" onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sabre.mod.uk/','_blank','scrollbars=yes,toolbar=yes,menubar=yes,resizable=yes,status=no,location=no,directories=no,width=600,height=800');return false;" target="_blank">http://www.sabre.mod.uk/</a></p><p><img alt="SaBRE" border="0" height="199" src="/files/images/SaBRE 1.jpg" width="275" /></p><p> </p><p><img alt="SaBRE" border="0" height="199" src="/files/images/SaBRE 2.jpg" width="275" /></p><p> </p><p><img alt="SaBRE" border="0" height="199" src="/files/images/SaBRE 3.jpg" width